Glaxo Holdings Plc &lt;GLXO.L> said it hasfiled an application to obtain a listing of its ordinary shareson the Tokyo Stock Exchange.    It said in a statement it expects to obtain the listing byby the end of the company's financial year on June 30.    No new shares will be issued in connection with the listingon the Tokyo exchange, Glaxo said.    On February 18 Glaxo said it was seeking to list itsAmerican Depositary receipts, now traded on the NASDAQ system,on the New York Stock Exchange. It also expected this listingto be in place by June 30. Reuter&#3;